#### Issue details

I was making a game, utilizing a [fixed timestep](http://gafferongames.com/game-physics/fix-your-timestep/) for the first time, when I noticed that when my player (a red rectangle) was moving, occasionally it would jump forward many extra pixels. Thinking it was the timestep, I tried many different things, but eventually found that for whatever reason Libgdx was just occasionally getting really high frame times, accompanied with FPS drop. As a test, I made a new blank Libgdx project with no tools checked and nothing but Desktop selected. This new project still had the occasional high frame times and FPS drops.
#### Reproduction steps/code

I've tested this on four different computers, all with the same results. This doesn't seem to be a universal problem (as many people have successfully developed with Libgdx), but I did find some threads (I would link, but I can't seem to find them right now) on the forums about what sounds like a similar issue, but they didn't come to a resolution. Below is a barebones version of the code I was using to see the problem. For my game I wanted vSync disabled and the framerate to be unlimited, but the problem occurs regardless of whether vSync is enabled or the framerate is limited. I've also included some logs of the output of the run of the below program. I've put the in delta time seconds, only so it's easier to read.

